I don't think we can know what it's like
when you're in love with someone...

1007
01:10:18,798 --> 01:10:20,164
And they change.

1008
01:10:30,518 --> 01:10:31,634
Hey, what's up, slut?

1009
01:10:31,728 --> 01:10:34,311
Hey, don't shame the slut.
Rhi, I'm proud of you.

1010
01:10:34,397 --> 01:10:35,387
Stay slutty.

1011
01:10:35,648 --> 01:10:37,389
Shut up, dumbass.

1012
01:10:41,279 --> 01:10:42,941
- Hi.
- Hi.

1013
01:10:44,699 --> 01:10:46,235
I really missed you yesterday.

1014
01:10:47,702 --> 01:10:49,614
I'm sorry about those guys.
It's my fault.

1015
01:10:50,455 --> 01:10:53,243
It's nothing. So tell me everything.

1016
01:10:58,629 --> 01:11:00,461
She's got more appointments tomorrow.

1017
01:11:00,923 --> 01:11:05,714
Doctors, maybe an overnight stay.
Probably she goes on medication.

1018
01:11:07,054 --> 01:11:10,468
I hope it turns out okay.
I mean, I think it could...

1019
01:11:11,684 --> 01:11:13,050
But it's her life, so...

1020
01:11:13,478 --> 01:11:16,846
It is. And you saved it.

1021
01:11:18,149 --> 01:11:19,310
You stayed.

1022
01:11:20,526 --> 01:11:21,858
I stayed.

1023
01:11:22,987 --> 01:11:26,526
So that means you can
stay in someone else, maybe?

1024
01:11:28,993 --> 01:11:30,575
Maybe I could.

1025
01:11:31,287 --> 01:11:32,869
What are you doing tonight?

1026
01:11:34,916 --> 01:11:36,202
Date.

1027
01:11:36,667 --> 01:11:38,078
Not with you.

1028
01:11:39,045 --> 01:11:40,707
With her boyfriend.
It's their anniversary.

1029
01:11:41,088 --> 01:11:42,670
I probably shouldn't miss it.

1030
01:11:43,716 --> 01:11:45,457
Well, maybe tomorrow then.

1031
01:11:53,309 --> 01:11:54,299
Can I kiss you?

1032
01:11:57,104 --> 01:11:58,094
Yeah.

1033
01:12:10,868 --> 01:12:11,858
Hi.

1034
01:12:14,080 --> 01:12:17,244
What are you doing up so late?
I thought you had a test tomorrow.

1035
01:12:19,126 --> 01:12:23,040
Mom, I know you and Dad
are trying to make it work.

1036
01:12:25,925 --> 01:12:31,466
But every day you can grow
a little bit closer to each other

1037
01:12:31,556 --> 01:12:35,175
or you can grow
a little bit farther apart.

1038
01:12:37,103 --> 01:12:38,139
Okay.

1039
01:12:39,272 --> 01:12:40,262
Um...

1040
01:12:42,358 --> 01:12:45,226
Look, I know Dad is not who he was.

1041
01:12:46,612 --> 01:12:49,195
But you're not who you were, either.

1042
01:12:50,616 --> 01:12:52,573
Because we all change.

1043
01:12:55,830 --> 01:12:58,573
And you've changed, too.

1044
01:13:01,335 --> 01:13:02,496
So...

1045
01:13:03,796 --> 01:13:05,128
Please, just grow closer.

1046
01:14:22,416 --> 01:14:23,952
He's amazing, Rhiannon.

1047
01:14:24,835 --> 01:14:28,704
He's curious and kind, and handsome.

1048
01:14:30,466 --> 01:14:33,459
It's funny, I've known him for so long,
but I don't know much about him.

1049
01:14:34,053 --> 01:14:35,134
He's so shy at school.

1050
01:14:35,221 --> 01:14:37,463
Yeah, he's not the kinda kid
that's built for high school.

1051
01:14:38,683 --> 01:14:40,015
He's built for what comes next.

1052
01:14:41,352 --> 01:14:44,220
He remembers
beautiful things beautifully.

1053
01:14:45,106 --> 01:14:46,597
He reads and he sees.

1054
01:14:46,691 --> 01:14:48,603
And he listens
with every part of himself.

1055
01:14:49,902 --> 01:14:52,269
He sees what's funny in people
without ever being cruel.

1056
01:14:52,905 --> 01:14:56,319
Excuse me, I'll take this guy
if you don't want him. Who is he?

1057
01:14:56,659 --> 01:14:58,275
Oh, he's talking about himself.

1058
01:14:58,661 --> 01:14:59,651
Oh.

1059
01:15:00,454 --> 01:15:01,570
Hi.

1060
01:15:06,585 --> 01:15:07,871
(BELL RINGS)

1061
01:15:10,798 --> 01:15:12,539
So, do you have plans after school?

1062
01:15:12,675 --> 01:15:14,416
Um, it is after school.

1063
01:15:18,180 --> 01:15:19,637
RHIANNON: What is happening?

1064
01:15:19,932 --> 01:15:21,343
Where are we going?

1065
01:16:24,371 --> 01:16:27,330
Do you think you could stay in Alexander
for one more day?

1066
01:16:30,711 --> 01:16:32,077
I'm not sure.

1067
01:16:34,006 --> 01:16:35,167
You did it with Kelsea.

1068
01:16:36,717 --> 01:16:39,004
With Kelsea it was easier,
I think, 'cause...

1069
01:16:40,096 --> 01:16:41,837
I guess she didn't wanna
be here anymore.

1070
01:16:44,058 --> 01:16:45,265
It's fine.

1071
01:16:46,227 --> 01:16:48,059
I get it. It's all good.

1072
01:16:53,734 --> 01:16:55,942
Would make things easier, though,
wouldn't it?

1073
01:17:00,866 --> 01:17:02,823
- (KNOCK AT DOOR)
- Rhi?

1074
01:17:04,245 --> 01:17:05,235
Hey.

1075
01:17:10,501 --> 01:17:12,743
(BELL RINGS)

1076
01:17:18,425 --> 01:17:21,668
Oh, my God. You stayed.

1077
01:17:23,222 --> 01:17:24,884
That's so exciting.

1078
01:17:34,108 --> 01:17:35,815
I knew exactly what it was.

1079
01:17:36,735 --> 01:17:37,976
Date night again tonight?

1080
01:17:38,487 --> 01:17:41,230
