1081
01:17:42,199 --> 01:17:43,360
Tomorrow.

1082
01:17:44,493 --> 01:17:45,950
Okay.

1083
01:17:53,419 --> 01:17:56,662
Hi. Someone's excited for learning.

1084
01:18:37,171 --> 01:18:38,457
I love you.

1085
01:18:39,340 --> 01:18:40,501
I love you, too.

1086
01:18:43,510 --> 01:18:46,127
I better get home,
or my mom will kill me.

1087
01:18:46,722 --> 01:18:48,429
Should we call it a night, then?

1088
01:18:50,726 --> 01:18:55,187
Actually, I guess I could come in
for, like, a minute.

1089
01:19:13,832 --> 01:19:16,119
- I think I should go now.
- Yeah.

1090
01:19:26,971 --> 01:19:30,214
Who forgets their own birthday?
Is that the new girl's fault?

1091
01:19:30,641 --> 01:19:32,132
Mom, I said I was sorry.

1092
01:19:32,726 --> 01:19:34,217
Past few days,
I don't even recognize you.

1093
01:19:34,311 --> 01:19:36,519
I don't know if this is some
teenage angst bullshit,

1094
01:19:36,605 --> 01:19:37,641
but I won't have it.

1095
01:19:37,731 --> 01:19:39,973
- Mom, please don't be mad.
- I'm not mad.

1096
01:19:41,443 --> 01:19:43,901
Your aunts and I cooked literally
all day preparing that dinner,

1097
01:19:43,988 --> 01:19:46,105
which was at your request.
All of your favorites.

1098
01:19:46,615 --> 01:19:47,981
I'm just disappointed.

1099
01:19:48,701 --> 01:19:50,784
That was a shitty, selfish thing
you did.

1100
01:19:54,456 --> 01:19:56,072
I'll make it up to them somehow.

1101
01:20:02,840 --> 01:20:04,547
You have a family that loves you.

1102
01:20:08,012 --> 01:20:09,844
Don't take that for granted.

1103
01:20:20,316 --> 01:20:22,478
- Hey.
- Hey.

1104
01:20:23,319 --> 01:20:25,106
Where have you been?
You weren't in class.

1105
01:20:25,446 --> 01:20:27,438
- Rhiannon...
- Did you get in trouble?

1106
01:20:27,656 --> 01:20:29,192
Not as much as you might think.

1107
01:20:29,658 --> 01:20:32,150
- Rhiannon.
- Hey, are we still on for tonight?

1108
01:20:33,704 --> 01:20:36,993
His parents went out of town.
So, my place at 8:00?

1109
01:20:37,082 --> 01:20:38,698
Yeah, great. I'll see you then.

1110
01:20:38,792 --> 01:20:40,033
Hey, Rebecca.

1111
01:20:42,755 --> 01:20:44,212
REBECCA: TGI Friday.

1112
01:20:45,799 --> 01:20:47,335
I've been a bad friend.

1113
01:20:48,177 --> 01:20:50,669
I'm sorry. I'll tell you everything.

1114
01:20:50,763 --> 01:20:52,174
I don't need an explanation.

1115
01:20:53,599 --> 01:20:55,682
Well, good, because I'm not really sure

1116
01:20:55,768 --> 01:20:57,851
I would give you one
that would make any sense.

1117
01:20:59,355 --> 01:21:00,971
Are you and Alexander a thing now?

1118
01:21:01,732 --> 01:21:03,724
Uh, yeah.

1119
01:21:04,318 --> 01:21:05,775
I always thought you should be together.

1120
01:21:06,612 --> 01:21:07,898
You did?

1121
01:21:08,113 --> 01:21:09,103
Yeah.

1122
01:21:10,908 --> 01:21:12,399
I'm glad you're happy, Rhi.

1123
01:21:13,369 --> 01:21:15,361
I got practice, so, gotta go.

1124
01:21:23,629 --> 01:21:24,619
(DOOR BELL RINGS)

1125
01:21:42,731 --> 01:21:43,721
Wow.

1126
01:21:43,941 --> 01:21:45,648
What is this, the Last Supper?

1127
01:21:46,485 --> 01:21:48,067
More like a first date.

1128
01:21:48,570 --> 01:21:51,529
Turns out, he's a really great cook.

1129
01:21:52,282 --> 01:21:53,818
He's a really great guy.

1130
01:21:54,284 --> 01:21:55,866
Okay. I know.

1131
01:21:56,912 --> 01:21:58,153
So are you.

1132
01:21:58,247 --> 01:22:02,241
I mean, really great. I've never had
your cooking, so I can't speak to that.

1133
01:22:03,419 --> 01:22:08,289
Rhiannon, he's got a family
that loves him, and that he loves.

1134
01:22:09,591 --> 01:22:11,173
It's everything I've ever wanted.

1135
01:22:12,386 --> 01:22:14,878
Yeah. It's been nice.

1136
01:22:16,223 --> 01:22:17,555
But it's not mine.

1137
01:22:20,102 --> 01:22:23,140
I'm forcing Alexander
out of his own life, and it's wrong.

1138
01:22:24,565 --> 01:22:26,522
And the longer I stay,
the more I'm damaging him.

1139
01:22:27,359 --> 01:22:29,021
We'll go back to how it was.

1140
01:22:31,780 --> 01:22:33,817
Do you know Flynn in my algebra class?

1141
01:22:35,200 --> 01:22:37,157
You cannot, under any circumstance,
be him.

1142
01:22:37,244 --> 01:22:39,907
If that's who you wake up in,
then don't even call me.

1143
01:22:43,667 --> 01:22:46,580
I mean, it can be Flynn.
It's not a deal-breaker.

1144
01:22:48,547 --> 01:22:50,334
I can't do it to anybody.

1145
01:22:54,303 --> 01:22:56,169
Not to Alexander, not to Flynn.

1146
01:22:58,640 --> 01:23:00,222
- Not to you.
- What are you saying?

1147
01:23:02,186 --> 01:23:04,473
I've been thinking about this over
and over and over.

1148
01:23:04,563 --> 01:23:06,020
I'm always going to be blocking you

1149
01:23:06,106 --> 01:23:07,642
from being with someone
who's perfect for you.

1150
01:23:14,573 --> 01:23:16,109
How could you say that?

1151
01:23:16,283 --> 01:23:18,775
Because Alexander's perfect for you.

1152
01:23:20,329 --> 01:23:22,446
- He's your type.
- You're my type.

1153
01:23:24,625 --> 01:23:26,787
Do you think I wanna live without you?

1154
01:23:28,587 --> 01:23:30,954
Do you think I'll ever be happy
in a place you're not?

1155
01:23:33,217 --> 01:23:35,254
Go back to a life that you're not in,

1156
01:23:35,344 --> 01:23:38,178
back to seeing only faces
that aren't yours?

1157
01:23:38,388 --> 01:23:40,505
Hearing only voices that aren't yours?

1158
01:23:43,727 --> 01:23:45,309
You should be with him.

1159
01:23:48,440 --> 01:23:51,933
He's tall, slim, nice shoulders.

1160
01:23:58,075 --> 01:23:59,691
He's really smart.

1161
01:24:01,411 --> 01:24:05,246
He's incredibly kind, he's interesting,
and thoughtful on so many levels.

1162
01:24:05,332 --> 01:24:08,450
No. We can make it work, A.

1163
01:24:08,544 --> 01:24:09,910
I wanna believe that.

1164
01:24:11,296 --> 01:24:12,878
You know I wanna believe that.

1165
01:24:26,645 --> 01:24:29,137
Think about what happens
if you and I stay together.

1166
01:24:29,481 --> 01:24:31,347
I mean, really, truly, imagine it.

1167
01:24:34,069 --> 01:24:35,526
What does that look like in a year?

1168
01:24:37,489 --> 01:24:38,479
In 10 years?

1169
01:24:38,907 --> 01:24:40,364
What will happen to your life

1170
01:24:40,534 --> 01:24:43,322
if I'm the person in the world
that you're closest to?

1171
01:24:43,745 --> 01:24:45,236
How alone will it make you...

1172
01:24:46,665 --> 01:24:48,577
<i>If the one that you love is me?</i>

1173
01:24:49,668 --> 01:24:53,332
<i>And the one that you're with is me.
And you can't tell anyone about me.</i>

1174
01:24:54,381 --> 01:24:56,873
<i>How much is that gonna cut you off
from your family?</i>

1175
01:24:58,468 --> 01:25:01,336
<i>How much is that gonna cut you off
from everyone you know?</i>

1176
01:25:06,226 --> 01:25:09,390
<i>And what happens when I start waking up
as someone in a marriage?</i>

1177
01:25:11,565 --> 01:25:13,227
<i>Someone with kids?</i>

1178
01:25:16,153 --> 01:25:17,689
<i>What if we want a kid?</i>

1179
01:25:21,033 --> 01:25:24,447
<i>How will it feel for you to raise
that kid almost entirely alone</i>

1180
01:25:24,536 --> 01:25:27,449
<i>and not be able to explain to anyone
why that's what you chose?</i>

1181
01:25:30,792 --> 01:25:32,454
<i>Whose kid is that gonna be?</i>

1182
01:25:34,588 --> 01:25:35,874
<i>Is that gonna be my kid?</i>

1183
01:25:37,924 --> 01:25:40,962
Or will she be the kid of some guy
that you'll never see again

1184
01:25:41,053 --> 01:25:43,340
while my kid leaves you
the day after she's born?

1185
01:25:44,181 --> 01:25:45,888
Will my kid ever know her parents?

1186
01:25:46,475 --> 01:25:48,683
Or is she gonna have a life like mine
and always wonder...

1187
01:25:48,769 --> 01:25:49,930
Stop.

1188
01:26:01,031 --> 01:26:04,024
Most people know that their first love
won't be their only love.

1189
01:26:07,621 --> 01:26:09,237
But for me, you're both.

1190
01:26:18,590 --> 01:26:19,922
Say something.

1191
01:26:35,691 --> 01:26:38,024
We have three hours until midnight.

1192
01:26:40,696 --> 01:26:42,562
Let's not waste it.

1193
01:26:47,244 --> 01:26:48,826
RHIANNON: What else?

1194
01:26:48,912 --> 01:26:52,656
A: In some minds, everything feels muted
and dim.

1195
01:26:52,749 --> 01:26:57,244
And in others, it's like everything
is supercharged and unfocused.

1196
01:26:57,963 --> 01:27:00,671
Like a radio flipping
from station to station.

1197
01:27:02,634 --> 01:27:04,091
Hard to get control of.

1198
01:27:06,054 --> 01:27:07,340
What else?

1199
01:27:08,974 --> 01:27:09,964
Um...

1200
01:27:11,560 --> 01:27:12,767
I'm thinking.

1201
01:27:19,776 --> 01:27:21,768
Am I going to see you again?

1202
01:27:29,161 --> 01:27:31,403
I have to believe that we will.

1203
01:27:33,832 --> 01:27:35,949
But you have to believe that we won't.

1204
01:27:41,089 --> 01:27:42,546
RHIANNON: <i>Where are you going to go?</i>

1205
01:27:44,676 --> 01:27:45,837
A: <i>Far away.</i>

1206
01:27:47,387 --> 01:27:48,548
<i>New York.</i>

1207
01:27:50,015 --> 01:27:51,631
<i>Chicago, if I can get there.</i>

1208
01:27:53,894 --> 01:27:57,934
<i>Just some big, dense city
where there's lots of people to be.</i>

1209
01:28:02,027 --> 01:28:04,644
<i>There's still some things
I need to figure out about myself.</i>

1210
01:28:09,951 --> 01:28:13,740
Make marks, okay? Leave traces.

1211
01:28:16,041 --> 01:28:17,031
Yeah.

1212
01:28:23,048 --> 01:28:24,255
It's time.

1213
01:28:31,264 --> 01:28:32,971
Will you remember this tomorrow?

1214
01:28:35,435 --> 01:28:36,721
I'll remember everything.

1215
01:28:39,022 --> 01:28:40,388
So will I.

1216
01:28:46,196 --> 01:28:48,108
This is the nice note.

1217
01:28:52,202 --> 01:28:53,409
Good night.

1218
01:29:13,974 --> 01:29:15,181
Good night.

1219
01:29:27,529 --> 01:29:31,489
(ALARM BEEPING)

1220
01:29:31,741 --> 01:29:32,948
KATIE'S MOM: Katie.

1221
01:29:34,077 --> 01:29:35,693
Katie, you up?

1222
01:29:40,959 --> 01:29:41,995
Katie.

1223
01:29:45,171 --> 01:29:47,163
(POP MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO)

1224
01:30:38,266 --> 01:30:39,347
Hi.

1225
01:30:41,937 --> 01:30:44,771
Has anyone ever told you,
you have a nice smile?

1226
01:30:58,244 --> 01:30:59,655
Just being honest.
